The auditorium is also used by the school for occasional assemblies and events, so you may run into a student or two. It's all good though - both the public and students are allowed to use the bathrooms.

name: Skatepark public toilets, Cowaramup
directions: Turn East into Hall Road off Bussel Highway, in the middle of Cowaramup.  The toilets are behind the old hall.  There is a bitumen path between the hall and the tennis courts.
comment: Open 24/7, but not lit at night.  Ample free parking, including disabled parking.

name: Margaret Rivermouth
directions: From Margaret River, turn West onto Wallcliffe Road off Bussel Highway.  At the T-junction with Caves Road turn left, then immediately turn right at the abandoned house.  Continue until you turn right onto Surfer's Point Road, then right at the roundabout onto Rivermouth Road.  Follow this road until it terminates in the Rivermouth carpark.  You will see the toilet block.
comment: Open 24/7.  The toilet block has no lights, so it's dark at night.  The change rooms are gendered. Ample free parking, but it may be full during summer.  There is another carpark further up the hill.

name: Cowaramup public toilets 2
street: Intersection of Memorial Drive and Miamup Road
directions: Turn West into Memorial Drive from Bussel Highway.  At the T-junction, the toilet is the small red brick building to your left.  Park in any of the open spaces around the large green sheds.
comment: Open 24/7.  Very basic facility, but clean and functional.  Plenty of free parking.  Not lit at night.  The area is very quiet and safe.

name: Department of Chemistry
directions: Head to the Chemistry Department reception.  Go through the automatic doors, past the blue reception wall (which is on the right) and take the corridor left.  This corridor is signposted B-block.  About 20 m down the corridor is the accessible and all genders welcome WC on the left hand side.
comment: This is only available to university members between 08:30 and 18:00, Monday - Friday.  Only Chemistry staff can access the department outside these times.  Chemistry students should also be aware that there are all genders WCs in F-block, the middle of D / E block, WACL, lower A and lower B blocks (CARD ACCESS ONLY!).

name: Cowaramup public toilets
directions: Turn into Hall Road off Bussel Highway.  The toilets are behind the old hall.  There is a bitumen path between the hall and tennis courts.
comment: Open 24/7, but not lit at night.  The area is quiet and very safe.  Ample free parking.

name: Margaret River Public Toilets
street: Intersection of Fearn Ave and Charles W Ave.
directions: Turn west on Fearn Ave. off Bussel Highway.  You will see the toilet block on your right in a carpark.
comment: Open 24/7.  There is plenty of free parking and the toilets are lit at night.  There is also a sharps disposal container.

name: Margaret River public toilets
street: Cnr Fearn Ave and Charles W Ave
directions: In the center of Margaret River, behind the shops on Bussel Hwy.  Turn west onto Fearn Ave off Bussel Hwy, the toilet block is in the car park to your right.
comment: Plenty of free parking and very close to shops  and cafes.   Open 24/7.  Well lit at night.  Also has a sharps disposal container.

name: Margaret River Mouth Beach
directions: From Margaret River, follow Wallcliffe Rd. towards Prevelly.  Turn right onto Surfers Point Rd., then right at the roundabout onto Rivermouth Rd.  Follow this down to the car park.   The toilet block is next to the car park.
comment: Open 24/7, but not lit at night. There's also a sharps disposal container.
